-= Kitchen =-

You can see a fridge. You bend down to tie your shoe. When you stand up, you notice an oven. You make out a table. You see a cookbook on the table. As if things weren't amazing enough already, you can even see a counter. The counter is vast. On the counter you see a knife. You make out a stove. What a great pairing of adjectives and nouns! But the thing hasn't got anything on it.

There is a closed plain door leading east. You don't like doors? Why not try going north, that entranceway is not blocked by one.
